This paper discusses techniques for adaptive query processing, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions data streams, which is a subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The optimization approaches mentioned in the paper involve pruning, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses implementation within a query processing system, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
